  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility package for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under VAD conditions. COU2 requires prediction of absolute hemolysis index values across pulsatile operating conditions at Model Risk Level 5. The validation result presented here references a steady-state benchtop comparator dataset whose flow regime (non-pulsatile, fixed-RPM) does not match the pulsatile, time-varying flow conditions declared in the COU. Additionally, one validation result object is emitted without a comparedAgainst link, triggering W-AR-05. Decision is recorded as Accepted despite the comparator mismatch and multiple credibility gaps, representing an undercutting inference-method mismatch (D3).",
